---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from "../consts";
const updated = "2026-06-25";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Exactly what Splander Jobs handles, where it lives, and what we do (and don't do) with it. Local-first by default — your job-search data never leaves your device."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16">
      <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-emerald-700">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 font-display text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <div class="prose-sj mt-8">
        <p>
          Splander Jobs is a Chrome extension that helps you track job applications you find on
          LinkedIn, Indeed, Glassdoor and jobnet.co.il. This page describes exactly what data the
          extension handles, where it lives, and what we do (and don't do) with it.
        </p>

        <h2>Summary, in one paragraph</h2>
        <p>
          Splander Jobs runs entirely in your browser. Every job you track is saved to
          <code>chrome.storage.local</code> on your own device. The extension does not have a
          server-side database of your applications, and we never see or transmit your job-search
          data. The only personal information that ever leaves your device is your email address,
          <strong>and only if</strong> you choose to submit it to the Premium waitlist. The extension
          also sends an anonymous, opt-out usage heartbeat (a random id + coarse counts, no personal
          data), and — only when you explicitly submit feedback — your message plus coarse,
          non-personal details.
        </p>

        <h2>What data we handle</h2>

        <h3>1. Job-application data</h3>
        <p>
          When you use Splander Jobs on a job page, the extension reads the page's contents — title,
          company, location, posting URL, salary, and similar fields — so it can attach a status pill
          and let you save it to your tracker.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Where it lives:</strong> <code>chrome.storage.local</code>, a sandboxed per-extension area of your own browser profile.</li>
          <li><strong>Where it does NOT live:</strong> Nowhere else. We do not send it to our servers, to a third party, or to anyone.</li>
          <li><strong>How long:</strong> Until you uninstall the extension or clear your browser profile.</li>
          <li><strong>Export / delete:</strong> Settings → Your data → Export JSON backup. Uninstalling or clearing extension storage deletes everything.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Premium waitlist email (only if you submit it)</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>If, and only if,</strong> you type your email and click "Join the waitlist", Splander
          Jobs sends that one email address to our Supabase project so we can notify you when Premium
          opens for beta access.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>What is sent:</strong> Your email, the app version, and your browser's User-Agent string. Nothing else.</li>
          <li><strong>What we do NOT use it for:</strong> Unrelated marketing, selling to third parties, or advertising.</li>
          <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Email <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a> and we'll remove your waitlist row and any associated auth user.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Splander Jobs Premium account (only if you sign in)</h3>
        <p>
          If you sign in, your settings (and, when you turn on sync, your job-application data) are
          mirrored to your Supabase Auth account so they roam across devices. Settings → Sign out
          clears the session; email us to delete the account and all rows associated with it.
        </p>

        <h3>4. Optional Gmail integration (you grant per-account)</h3>
        <p>
          Settings → Gmail lets you connect a Gmail account so Splander Jobs can detect recruiter
          replies and auto-advance your status. This uses Google's read-only Gmail scope
          (<code>gmail.readonly</code>), runs entirely in your browser, and forwards nothing
          off-device. Disconnect any time. The Chrome Web Store build is <strong>read-only</strong>
          with respect to your Gmail — it never writes, sends, deletes, or edits anything.
        </p>

        <h3>5. Anonymous usage analytics (on by default, you can opt out)</h3>
        <p>
          The extension sends a once-a-day anonymous "heartbeat". Turn it off any time in
          <strong>Settings → About → "Share anonymous usage data"</strong>.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>What is sent:</strong> A random install id (not derived from you or your device), app version, browser language, OS, plan tier, and three coarse flags (sync on/off, Gmail connected, a bucketed job-count range).</li>
          <li><strong>What is NOT sent:</strong> No email, no job/company/CV/message content, no URLs, no page contents — ever.</li>
          <li><strong>No third-party analytics SDK</strong> is embedded.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6. Feedback you submit (only when you send it)</h3>
        <p>
          The feedback form — in the extension and on this website — sends your message to our Supabase
          project <strong>only when you click Send</strong>. Nothing is sent just for opening the page.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>What is sent:</strong> Your message text (only what you type), an optional email if you provide one for a reply, and coarse non-personal details — app/page, browser language, and the page you were on.</li>
          <li><strong>What is NOT sent:</strong> No job/company/CV/email content, no page contents, no diagnostic logs.</li>
          <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Email <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What we do NOT do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>No third-party analytics SDKs</strong> (no Google Analytics, Mixpanel, Segment, or similar).</li>
          <li><strong>No advertising</strong> — we don't sell access to your data.</li>
          <li><strong>No automated apply</strong> — Splander Jobs never submits applications or sends messages on your behalf.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>Splander Jobs does not set cookies. It uses <code>chrome.storage.local</code> for its own state. This website sets no advertising or tracking cookies.</p>

        <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>Splander Jobs is intended for job seekers, who are typically adults. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>We will update this page when the data practices change. The "Last updated" date reflects the most recent revision.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>For privacy questions or data-deletion requests, email us at <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
